node.text:
CROWLERS ARE BACK! 🥳
.
A new crowler machine has arrived and we’re excited to announce that crowlers are available again in the Tasting Room.
.
Take home fresh draft beer straight from the source!
.
In celebration of the new crowler machine and holiday weekend, we are offering 3 for $30 crowlers through July 5th. Some exclusions apply.
.
Head to our story to check out our current draft list! @alesmithbrewing

We invite you to join us for our signature 3-Day San Diego Beer Week event, Speedway Grand Prix. 3 Days. 4 Laps. 16 Speedway Stout Variants.

Take up to 4 laps (aka flights) around the proverbial track to experience 16 limited Speedway Stout offerings. Beers for the flights are brewed from ideas submitted by the whole AleSmith team, with the 4th trip around the track being a VIP lap of barrel-aged variants, some being previous years' winning variants.

Fans are invited to come try all 16 variants and vote on each one. The winners you pick might even end up as a future special release!

Ready to have your beer palates racing? List of variants in each lap are listed on ticket event page. Please join us for our Speedway Grand Prix by purchasing lap tickets via highlighted IG story in our bio.

🏆 Today marks the anniversary of the Legendary Tony Gwynn's 2000th AND 3000th hits! 😲⁠
⁣⁠
On August 6th 1993 & 1999, six years apart, Tony struck a 2000 and then 3000 hit career milestone only reached by 22 other players before him.⁠
⁣⁠
And as if that wasn't enough, August 6th is also Tony's mother Vandella Gwynn's birthday! All in all a very special day in San Diego indeed.⁠
⁣⁠
Celebrate Mr. Padre's life with an engraved tile in the Tony Gwynn Museum, located within the AleSmith tasting room with proceeds from every tile purchased being donated to the Tony Gwynn Legacy Fund. ♥️⚾⁠
⁣⁠
Head to the link in our bio to learn more!⁠

Our 3rd #SpeedwayStout variant is here, and for this special edition release we were inspired by our neighbors to the south! 🇲🇽⁠
⁣⁠
We combined the comforting trio of Mexican dark chocolate, sea salt, and Mexican coffee to give the beer delectable notes of cacao + dark fruit, a subtle touch of cinnamon, & a kiss of roasty earthiness.⁠
⁣⁠
The coffee for this variant has low acidity with a full body packing solid milk chocolate sweetness and a nice cheery finish. ⁠
⁠
Mark your calendar for Speedway Grand Prix during the height of San Diego Beer Week this November for an event PACKED with awesome Speedway variants like this!⁠
⁣⁠
To find Speedway with Mexican Dark Chocolate, Sea Salt, and Mexican Coffee, head to the linkin.bio for our beer finder!⁠
